title: Breaking The Code - Radio Drama
description:
1 x 110 mins

A fact based play by the always good Hugh Whitemore.

Alan Turing, often called the father of computing, committed suicide in 1954 after being caught looking for casual homosexual sex in a Manchester toilet. The play tells the story of his work during WW2 at Bletchley Park as part of the UK government's team working on breaking German codes, in part through flashbacks from 1954 to his life as a teenager and his time at Blletchley.

Fascinating listening
